    {
      "id": "a93b8de95c2ceaf17d990214b413e30559c9c364",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-12 16:37:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI like that all of these patches include the kernel commit which includes this change.  Normally when a method like this is renamed, there is a reason for the change, but I don't see any changes in the rest of the code?\n\nInstead of having inline #ifdefs, I would prefer to have a macro in lustre_compat25.h that maps d_make_root() to d_alloc_root() for older kernels. This keeps the code cleaner, and avoids the need to change the code for upstream submission.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6ed90a99c899e75daff072ba1c5fd97bf334fe76",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 242,
        "name": "Liu Xuezhao",
        "email": "xuezhao.liu@emc.com",
        "username": "XuezhaoLiu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-05 07:16:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"Normally when a method like this is renamed, there is a reason for the change, but I don't see any changes in the rest of the code?\"\n\nThe difference bewteen d_make_root and d_alloc_root is d_make_root() drops the reference to inode if dentry allocation fails. Kernel commit adc0e91ab142abe93f5b0d7980ada8a7676231fe introduces d_make_root, and several commits after that changes to d_make_root finally commit 32991ab305ace7017c62f8eecbe5eb36dc32e13b removes d_alloc_root.\n\n\"Instead of having inline #ifdefs, I would prefer to have a macro in lustre_compat25.h that maps d_make_root() to d_alloc_root() for older kernels.\"\n\nWill update it, thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
